16. Bxh6 { With a half-open f-file this typical sacrifice works like a charm. }
16... gxh6
{ 16...Nxd3  17.cxd3  gxh6  18.h3!   18.Qxh6?  Nh5!  19.Rf5  Ng7-+  Nh5   18...Bd7  19.Qxh6+-  19.Qf2+- }
17. Qxh6 Nxd3
{ 17...Bf8  18.Qxf6  Qxf6  19.Rxf6  Nxd3  20.cxd3  Bg7  21.Rf4+- } 18. Qg5+
{ But be careful, the automatic   18.cxd3?  fails to  18...Nh5-+  and Black defends. }
18... Kh8 19. cxd3
{ White soon will bring down Black's open king. A sample line could be  19...Rc8  20.Rf4  Rc5  21.Nd5+-  and Black's defense will collapse.   19...Rg8  20.Qh6+  Nh7  21.Rxf7+- }
