18... h5 { 18...Ncd7  19.Qh6+  Kg8  20.Re3+- } 19. Bh6+
{ Again, White has to be diligent.   19.Re3?  Nfe4  20.Bxe4  Nxe4  21.Rxe4  Rc8  22.c3  f6-+  sees Black come out on top. }
19... Kh8 { 19...Kxh6  20.Qg5 } 20. Bxf8
{ White achieved material balance. The black king stays exposed and will lead to Black's downfall, e.g.   20...Bxd5  21.Bg7+  Kxg7  22.Qg5+  Kf8  23.Qh6+  Kg8  24.Bh7++-   20.Bg7+?  Kxg7  21.Qg5+  Kh8  22.Qh6+  Kg8=  is only a perpetual. }
