{ Lets start with an example that is both positional and tactical. } 16... Rxc3
17. bxc3 { 17.Bxf6  Nxf6  18.bxc3  Nxe4-+ } 17... Nxe4
{ As a general rule, ruining the pawn structure and winning the e4-pawn is already enough to justify the exchange sac. Here Black is getting even more. }
18. Bxd8
{ After   18.Be3  Qc7!  Black again has more than enough positional compensation and gets even more.  19.c4  Nc3!  20.Bd3  e4  21.Bd2  Bf6  22.Qe1  a5-+  Black wins a piece! }
18... Nxf2+
{ 18...Rxd8  19.Qe1  a5  20.Na2∓  is the positional solution. Again, one pawn plus the ruined pawn structure is more than enough compensation. }
19. Kg1 { 19.Rxf2  Qxf2-+  Black ends up two pawns to the good. } 19... Nh3+
20. Kh1 Qg1+ 21. Rxg1 Nf2# *

