12. Nf5 exf5
{ Black can't leave the knight on f5   12...Bf8  13.Rxd6  Bxd6  14.Nxg7+  Kf8  15.Qxf6+- }
13. Bxf6
{ 13.e5?  is answered by  13...Bb7  The resulting position after  14.exf6  Nxb3+  15.axb3  Bxf3  16.Rxe7+  Kf8  17.gxf3=  is evaluated as even by the engine. }
13... gxf6 { 13...Nxb3+  doesn't change much  14.axb3  gxf6  15.Nd5+- } 14. Nd5
{ 14.Bxf7+  Kxf7  15.Qh5+  Kg7  16.exf5+-  is very strong, too } 14... Qd8 15.
Nxe7
{ 15.exf5?  Bb7∓   15.Qh5?  Nxb3+  16.axb3  f4  17.e5!  fxe5  18.Rxe5  dxe5  19.Qxe5  f6  and Black is still in the game after  20.Nc7+  Qxc7  21.Qxc7  Kf7= }
15... Qxe7 { 15...Kxe7  16.exf5+  Kf8  17.Qxa8+- } 16. exf5 *

