{ This isn't a clearly winning tactic in the sense that White has won material or mates in the final position. The motif is so important though that we have to implement this strike into this course. }
11. Bxe6
{ A very typical sacrifice which leads to a winning position for White. } 11...
fxe6 12. Nxe6 Qc8 13. Nxg7+
{ The material is balanced as White has three pawns for the bishop. However, Black's pawn protection is destroyed and the d6-pawn is weak. Eventually, White's pieces will break through and hunt down Black's king. }
*

