11. Nxc6
{ 11.Bxb5?  axb5  12.Ndxb5  Qb6  As long as Black's king isn't in trouble, keeping the queens on in such positions is often a good idea.   12...Qb8?!  13.Nxd6+  Bxd6?  14.Qxd6  Qxd6  15.Rxd6±  is good for White. In an endgame, he can make good use of his three passers.  13.Nxd6+  Kf8∓  This is a typical example when Bxb5 wasn't too good of an idea. White will have problems pushing his passers without exposing his king and Black will slowly but surely mount an attack with his extra piece. Black is clearly for choice here. }
11... Qxc6 12. e5 { 12.Bf3+-  is good, too. } *

