[FEN "2rb1rk1/3q1p1p/p2p1Pp1/1b2p1P1/1p2P3/1N4N1/PPP3QP/1K1R2R1 w - - 0 25"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White's idea is clear, to bring the queen to h6! } 25. Nf5 gxf5 26. Qh3 Kh8
{ 26...Qc6  27.Qh6  Qxc2+  28.Ka1+- } 27. exf5
{ No rush. Now Qh6 followed by Rg3 is a huge threat.  After the immediate   27.Qh6  Rg8  there is no good continuation.  28.Rg3  fxe4  29.Rh3  Qf5-+ }
27... Rg8
{ There are a lot of other moves for Black, but they are all refuted in basically the same way.   27...Be2  28.Rxd6  Qxd6  29.g6  fxg6  30.fxg6  Rc7  31.g7+  Kg8  32.gxf8=Q+  Kxf8  33.Qh6++-   27...Qc7  the only move to prevent Rg3, but White simply consolidates with  28.Rd2+-  and Rg3 again is unstoppable.   27...Re8  28.Rg3 }
28. Rg3 { The threat is Qxh7+.   28.Qh6  is still too early.  28...Qxf5-+ }
28... Bxf6 29. gxf6 Rxg3 30. hxg3 { White will double on the h-file. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
