[SetUp "1"]

25. Rxf6 { Not surprising. } 25... gxf6 { 25...Qxf6  26.Qxd7+- } 26. Qf5
{ But this isn't easy to find. White attacks the d3-knight and introduces the idea of Ng4-Nxf6. Black has a bunch of tries that ultimately all fail. }
26... Bxd5
{ 26...Ne5  stops Ng4, but allows  27.Ne4+-  and there is no sensible way to stop Nxf6.   26...Rxe3  is the most tenacious according to the machine.  27.Rxe3  Bxd5  28.Rh3  Nf2+   28...Qg8  29.Rg3+-  29.Qxf2  Be6  30.Ne4  Bxh3  31.gxh3  Qe7  32.Ng3+-  and even though he isn't down material Black is a lot worse due to his weak king.   26...Nc5  27.Ng4  Rxe2  28.Nxf6  Kg7  29.Qxh7+  Kxf6  30.Qh6+  Ke7  31.Bg5++-   26...Re5  27.Qxd3+-   26...Rxd5  27.Ncxd5!  Bxd5  28.Nxd5  Rxe2  29.Nxf6  transposes to 26...Bxd5. }
27. Ncxd5
{ 27.Nexd5?  fails to a deep counterattack  27...Rxe2  28.Nxf6  Nf2+  29.Kg1  Nh3+!  30.gxh3  Qb6+  31.Kh1  Rxh2+  32.Kxh2  Rxd2+  33.Kh1  Qc6+  34.Nfe4  f6=  White's king is too weak to play for a win. }
27... Rxd5 { 27...Re5  28.Qxd3+- } 28. Nxd5 Rxe2 29. Nxf6
{ 29.Qxd3??  Re5  30.Nb4  Qxd3  31.Nxd3  Rd5-+ } 29... Nf2+
{ 29...Rxd2  30.Qxh7 } 30. Kg1 Qd3
{ 30...Kg7  31.Qxh7+  Kxf6   31...Kf8  32.Bb4++-  32.Qh4++- } 31. Qc8+ Kg7 32.
Nh5+ { after  32...Kg6  33.Nf4+  picks up the queen. } *

